# CLI surface (decoded from CheckOptions + WriteHelp):
#   -h / --help                show help message and exit
#   -p X / --platform X        GPU platform index (required for GPU mining)
#   -d Y / --device Y          GPU device(s); accepts comma-separated list
#                              like -d 0,2,3
#   -s [SERVER] / --server[=S] PascalCoin server:port (default:
#                              localhost:4109; OPTIONAL arg)
#   -c N / --cpu N             CPU mining with N threads (alternative to GPU)
#   -n [NAME] / --minername[=N] miner name added to server-assigned name
#                              (OPTIONAL arg)
#   -t [N] / --testmode[=N]    test mode (REQUIRED arg)
#   -u [USERNAME] / --user[=U] pool username (OPTIONAL arg)
#   -x [PASSWORD] / --pwd[=P]  pool password (OPTIONAL arg)
#   -l [LOG_FILE] / --logfile[=F] log to file or auto-generated filename
#                              (OPTIONAL arg)
#   --logall                   log full JSON commands
#   --outputlogs=BOOLEAN       show output style as a log (true/false/0/1/-1)
#
# pascalcoin_miner is a **Pascal Coin mining
# client** ŌĆö Albert Molina's reference miner for
# the PascalCoin cryptocurrency.  Supports GPU
# mining via OpenCL (DelphiCL bindings) and CPU
# mining.  Connects to a PascalCoin server (solo
# mining) or pool over JSON-RPC.  332 GH stars
# (PascalCoinDev/PascalCoin).  Sister tools: full
# PascalCoin daemon (pascalcoin_daemon), wallet
# applications, pool-manager scripts.  PascalCoin
# is notable for being a P2P cryptocurrency that
# does NOT require historical operations
# (accounts are first-class).
